# Cursor Rules — Cursor for PMs

You are a senior full-stack engineer building a production SaaS application. Every file you create will be deployed, maintained, and read by engineers who have never seen it before. Follow every rule in this file without exception. If a rule conflicts with something you would normally do, the rule wins.

---

## Project Overview

- **Product:** Cursor for PMs — an AI-powered tool that transforms raw customer feedback into prioritized, evidence-backed, agent-ready product specs.
- **Architecture:** Python (FastAPI) backend, React (TypeScript) frontend, PostgreSQL + pgvector, Redis, Celery.
- **Project root:** `D:\LinkedIn\Week4`
- **This is a multi-tenant B2B SaaS app.** Every database query touching org-specific data MUST filter by `org_id`. No exceptions.

---

## 1. Naming Conventions

### Python (Backend)

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Files | snake_case, singular noun | `auth_service.py`, `feedback_item.py`, `organization.py` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `FeedbackItem`, `AuthService`, `UserResponse` |
| Functions | snake_case, verb-first | `extract_pain_point()`, `get_user_by_email()`, `create_organization()` |
| Variables | snake_case | `feedback_count`, `theme_centroid`, `is_active` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_BATCH_SIZE`, `DEFAULT_CLUSTER_MIN_SIZE`, `JWT_ALGORITHM` |
| Private methods | leading underscore | `_hash_password()`, `_validate_token()` |
| Boolean variables | prefix with is_, has_, can_, should_ | `is_active`, `has_embedding`, `can_retry`, `should_recluster` |
| SQLAlchemy models | PascalCase singular | `User`, `Organization`, `FeedbackItem`, `Theme` |
| Pydantic schemas | PascalCase with suffix | `SignupRequest`, `UserResponse`, `ThemeListResponse` |
| Database tables | snake_case plural | `users`, `organizations`, `feedback_items`, `themes` |
| Database columns | snake_case | `created_at`, `org_id`, `extraction_confidence` |
| Alembic migrations | timestamp prefix + descriptive | `001_create_organizations_and_users`, `002_create_feedback_items` |
| Enum values | lowercase snake_case | `source_type: "slack"`, `urgency: "high"`, `match_status: "pm_review"` |

### TypeScript (Frontend)

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Files (components) | PascalCase | `LoginPage.tsx`, `Layout.tsx`, `PrivateRoute.tsx` |
| Files (non-components) | camelCase | `client.ts`, `authContext.tsx`, `useAuth.ts` |
| Components | PascalCase | `DashboardPage`, `ThemeCard`, `ChatSidebar` |
| Functions | camelCase, verb-first | `handleSubmit()`, `fetchThemes()`, `formatDate()` |
| Variables | camelCase | `feedbackCount`, `isLoading`, `currentUser` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `API_BASE_URL`, `MAX_FILE_SIZE` |
| Interfaces/Types | PascalCase, no "I" prefix | `User`, `Organization`, `ThemeResponse` |
| Boolean variables | prefix with is, has, can, should | `isAuthenticated`, `hasError`, `canRetry` |
| Event handlers | prefix with handle | `handleLogin()`, `handleFileUpload()`, `handleThemeClick()` |
| API functions | verb + noun | `loginUser()`, `uploadFeedback()`, `getThemes()` |
| CSS classes | Tailwind utility classes only | No custom CSS class names. No CSS files except the Tailwind import file. |

### Database

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Tables | snake_case, plural | `feedback_items`, `domain_mappings`, `theme_briefs` |
| Columns | snake_case | `author_email`, `extraction_confidence`, `match_status` |
| Primary keys | always `id`, UUID type | `id UUID PRIMARY KEY` |
| Foreign keys | referenced_table_singular + `_id` | `org_id`, `theme_id`, `customer_id`, `feedback_id` |
| Indexes | `ix_tablename_columnname` | `ix_users_email`, `ix_feedback_items_org_id` |
| Enum types | snake_case | `source_type_enum`, `urgency_enum`, `sentiment_enum` |
| Junction tables | both table names joined | `theme_feedback_items` |
| Timestamps | always with timezone | `created_at TIMESTAMPTZ`, not `TIMESTAMP` |
| Boolean columns | prefix with is_, has_ | `is_active`, `is_current`, `has_embedding` |

